race.description: Btc Constructions Melbourne Cup Day On Sale Hcp (58)
race.comment: PEACE BABY (2) resumes and is having his first run for the Chloe Baxter yard after the switch from a Victorian stable. Hasn't raced since finishing fifth in stronger than this on the Pakenham Synthetic. Hasn't trialled publicly but has placed fresh and is well-placed. The betting will be key. DEBATING (1) needed the first-up outing. He's placed 3/4 second-up and his best form would see him right in it. 3x winning rider Jarrod Todd stays aboard. JUMPING POWER TWO (3) resumes and has switched from a Victorian barn. He's won fresh and has shown enough to keep very safe. DANCER FOR MONEY (4) had better support last time but faded after leading them up. Keeps the 3kg claim and won't be too far away. The remaining pair are struggling.
